Subject: Windows 2003 win2k.sys vulnerability






BRIEF SYNOPSIS



SUMMARY

     Under Windows NT5.2, all software that uses "EngTextOut" are
     exposed to BSOD when attempting to print non-ASCII characters.


POINT OF INTEREST

     "win32k.sys" at 0xbf8bc8d7 (Tue Mar 25 00:40:49 2003).


IMPLICATIONS

     Envisage it.


SYSTEMS AFFECTED

     Windows 2003 web server/server/enterprise (RTM and all betas)
     Windows .NET (all betas)
     Windows Whistler (all betas)


SYSTEMS NOT AFFECTED

     Windows 2000 SP3 and earlier
     Windows NT4
     Windows 9x




